1
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,670
[Bloom Life]

2
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:42,710
[2014]

3
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:44,590
Her efforts

4
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,950
made those who stuck to the old ways

5
00:01:46,970 --> 00:01:48,300
feel even more ashamed.

6
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:51,350
Her failure speaks louder
than the stagnant comfort

7
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:53,390
of those who never move forward.

8
00:01:53,870 --> 00:01:54,710
Well written.

9
00:01:56,009 --> 00:01:56,340
Go.

10
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:57,900
Go and exchange it for another book.

11
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:58,509
Okay.

12
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:01,100
Minawar.

13
00:02:01,110 --> 00:02:01,710
I wrote it.

14
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:07,870
In my memory,

15
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:10,800
going to my middle school
Chinese teacher

16
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,330
Ms. Li's house for tutoring

17
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:15,610
was like a ray of light breaking

18
00:02:15,930 --> 00:02:17,860
into our otherwise routine lives.

19
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:20,890
Her bookcase became my secret garden.

20
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,900
There,

21
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:26,150
we read de Beauvoir's "The Second Sex,"

22
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:29,130
encountered Jane Eyre's defiance,

23
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:32,030
and witnessed Sanmao's drifting life.

24
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:32,930
Ms. Li,

25
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:34,320
I don't understand.

26
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,360
Ms. Wang had already taken her child

27
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,740
and left her first abusive husband.

28
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:41,150
Why did she enter marriage again

29
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:42,600
to suffer once more?

30
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,130
When women

31
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:46,150
become the deepest bearers of suffering,

32
00:02:46,150 --> 00:02:47,750
the first step of their awakening is

33
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:50,079
to admit the real existence of suffering.

34
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,460
Xiao Hong used her pen

35
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:54,340
to etch an indelible tombstone

36
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:55,570
for those

37
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,060
silent Ms. Wangs.

38
00:02:58,079 --> 00:02:58,570
Laili.

39
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:00,120
Ms. Li.

40
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:00,890
Your notes.

41
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:03,710
I didn't bring them.

42
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:04,540
You didn't write any.

43
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:06,070
I really didn't bring them.

44
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,990
I wrote them at Arzugul's house.

45
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:09,900
Yesterday.

46
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,650
Yes. She wrote them at my house.

47
00:03:13,070 --> 00:03:15,120
Okay. Then tell me,

48
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:17,670
which character in the novel do you like?

49
00:03:20,860 --> 00:03:21,920
The painter Lily.

50
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,440
Ms. Li, I actually also think sometimes

51
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,970
Why haven't I thought
about creating myself?

52
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:31,110
Mom, I'm back.

53
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,180
Xia Zi?

54
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:38,860
Fang Nan?

55
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:58,240
[Episode 7: The A and B Roles of Life]

56
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:06,320
♪ That familiar red apple ♪

57
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:13,550
♪ Just like my lover's red face ♪

58
00:04:13,570 --> 00:04:17,370
♪ The tender whisper of the lover ♪

59
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:20,700
♪ is as sweet as sugar ♪

60
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:24,550
♪ The tender whisper of the lover ♪

61
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:27,990
♪ is as sweet as sugar ♪

62
00:04:28,020 --> 00:04:31,480
♪ A lover like pomegranate ♪

63
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:38,500
♪ A lover like a balsam flower ♪

64
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:40,570
It's so pretty.

65
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,540
Minawar has great taste.

66
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,360
You just finished
your postpartum confinement.

67
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,760
Are you adapting to work?

68
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,790
Not bad.

69
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,930
I really envy you.

70
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:51,000
We are exhausted every day.

71
00:04:51,370 --> 00:04:52,100
I didn't expect

72
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,960
"Alip and Sänäm" to be so popular.

73
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,800
It was tiring enough after the tour.

74
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,100
The extra performances are over,

75
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,920
and now they're throwing
in some kind of wrap-up show.

76
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:03,130
Thankfully, the last few shows
are in Kashgar.

77
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:05,260
I really don't want to travel anymore.

78
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:06,240
Dear,

79
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,840
help me zip up my dress.

80
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:14,360
You were the one

81
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:17,650
who told Sadiq and my mother-in-law,
weren't you?

82
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,890
What are you even talking about?

83
00:05:20,940 --> 00:05:22,350
Take good care of the child.

84
00:05:22,350 --> 00:05:23,550
Don't think too much.

85
00:05:31,110 --> 00:05:33,440
You're not the only one
who can play Sänäm.

86
00:05:34,530 --> 00:05:35,990
How am I any worse than you?

87
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:39,330
Why am I always just your understudy?

88
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,440
Come back quickly to feed the baby.

89
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,190
The baby threw up again.

90
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:58,750
The baby won't sleep

91
00:05:58,750 --> 00:05:59,950
and just keeps crying

92
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:23,970
Hello, Auntie. Hello, Laili.

93
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:24,620
Hello.

94
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:28,950
Come on in.

95
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,010
Your dad, really.

96
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,230
I asked him to buy a honeydew melon.

97
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,060
Why hasn't he come back for so long?

98
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:38,870
I'll go take a look.

99
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:39,990
I'll go.

100
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,060
Dad.

101
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:48,180
Dad.

102
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:51,720
Dad!

103
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,860
What's wrong with you?

104
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,270
Somebody!

105
00:06:56,510 --> 00:06:57,630
Help!

106
00:06:58,130 --> 00:06:58,740
Dad.

107
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:14,080
Mom.

108
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,730
How is your dad doing today?

109
00:07:17,210 --> 00:07:18,270
The doctor said

110
00:07:18,290 --> 00:07:19,960
my dad is out of danger.

111
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,620
The rest is just

112
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:24,280
a matter of time for recovery.

113
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:25,950
He will slowly get better.

114
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,810
Then you should rest early, too.

115
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:30,510
You've stayed up for 3 days.

116
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:32,120
Your body won't handle it.

117
00:07:32,180 --> 00:07:33,460
I'm fine, Mom.

118
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:34,500
Go and rest.

119
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,050
Okay, you rest first.

120
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:36,540
Okay.

121
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,370
Laili.

122
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,000
What is it?

123
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:55,940
Have a bite

124
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:57,880
while it's warm.

125
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,310
I'm fine. I'm not hungry.

126
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:00,450
Your health is the most important.

127
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:01,160
You should eat something.

128
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,420
I'm really not hungry.

129
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:06,740
What are your plans for the future?

130
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:10,530
Master can't make earthenware anymore.

131
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,360
The shop is going to close.

132
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,430
It won't close.

133
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:14,680
I'll figure something out.

134
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:17,330
How are you going
to keep the shop afloat?

135
00:08:17,450 --> 00:08:18,800
I admit you're better than me.

136
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,560
And you look down on me.

137
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,290
I have never looked down on you.

138
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,560
Really, Mulading.

139
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:26,330
I've envied you since I was little
because you can make earthenware.

140
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:28,530
It's true that I just started learning.

141
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:29,890
So,

142
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,090
I want to ask you for a favor.

143
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:35,679
Teach me how to make earthenware.

144
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:38,549
Why should I help you?

145
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:40,450
Who will help me?

146
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,049
Have you ever asked me

147
00:08:43,049 --> 00:08:44,010
what I want?

148
00:08:45,470 --> 00:08:47,510
But that was all my dad's idea.

149
00:08:47,850 --> 00:08:49,650
That guy from the instrument shop

150
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:51,310
does have his carving skills.

151
00:08:52,130 --> 00:08:54,790
But his hands are meant
for making instruments.

152
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,370
Are you really willing to let
those instrument-making hands

153
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,120
soak in mud all day?

154
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:00,550
If you don't want the shop to close,

155
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:02,150
What you need right now is me.

156
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,940
Master has fallen ill.

157
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:09,670
He can no longer make earthenware.

158
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:13,790
You need to face reality.

159
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,500
Aletong.

160
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:14,500
The noodles you made today
are so delicious.

161
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:15,960
I've already eaten 2 plates.

162
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,960
Did Nur make the noodles, or did you?

163
00:10:18,370 --> 00:10:19,890
Of course, Nur made them.

164
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:22,700
Nur makes the noodles,
and you eat them, right?

165
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:27,880
Look, look.

166
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:31,370
Today, Dali police received
a report from the public.

167
00:10:31,370 --> 00:10:33,960
A homestay owner defrauded
local residents of their homes.

168
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,790
Under the pretext of opening a homestay,

169
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:38,650
he illegally misappropriated
nearly half a million yuan.

170
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:39,430
500,000?

171
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:40,480
He ran away.

172
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,220
When did Zhou leave?

173
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,650
Did anything happen to him?

174
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:48,960
I don't think Zhou

175
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,620
would do something like this.

176
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:51,890
I believe him.

177
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:54,440
You can't judge a book by its cover.

178
00:10:54,660 --> 00:10:55,480
He won't run away.

179
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,410
He absolutely would
do something like this.

180
00:10:57,410 --> 00:10:59,290
It's just the doing of a few individuals.

181
00:10:59,290 --> 00:11:01,600
But it's been so long,

182
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:04,710
and he hasn't let
the renovation team resume work.

183
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,200
Keep your voice down.

184
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,720
Don't make Arzugul worry.

185
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,890
From my interactions with him,

186
00:11:11,890 --> 00:11:14,120
I think he has a great character.

187
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:16,150
So I believe him.

188
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:58,570
This instrument seems
a bit smaller than usual.

189
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,530
Because it's for a female customer,

190
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:05,380
it's made a bit smaller.

191
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:10,510
How is Uncle Batur?

192
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:11,550
He's doing well.

193
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,030
Have you decided

194
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:16,630
what pattern to carve?

195
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,720
Not yet. So I made this first.

196
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,960
How about a pomegranate pattern?

197
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,720
When we first met,

198
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,360
you gave me a pomegranate.

199
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:32,240
Pomegranate flowers are nice.

200
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:32,870
Okay.

201
00:12:33,870 --> 00:12:35,670
Pomegranate flowers are great.

202
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,820
Wait for me a sec.

203
00:12:41,820 --> 00:12:42,220
Okay.

204
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:24,210
What's wrong?

205
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,320
Nothing.

206
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,360
I have things to do at home.

207
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,820
I'm heading back now. Bye.

208
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:06,820
♪ We swore we'd never part ♪

209
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:13,910
♪ Sharing good times, our love was true ♪

210
00:15:16,130 --> 00:15:22,740
♪ A long-held wish seemed to come true ♪

211
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:28,230
♪ But fate was far too cruel ♪

212
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,570
Dad.

213
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:35,980
♪ A long-held wish seemed to come true ♪

214
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:42,230
♪ But fate was far too cruel ♪

215
00:15:38,820 --> 00:15:41,630
Laili didn't answer my call.

216
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:50,230
♪ Bound together like Laili and Majnun ♪

217
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,440
She won't see me, either.

218
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,860
What should I do?

219
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:57,490
♪ Lingering like lovers,
wasting time away ♪

220
00:15:57,510 --> 00:16:03,740
♪ Bound together like Laili and Majnun ♪

221
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:10,240
♪ Lingering like lovers,
wasting time away ♪

222
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:17,240
♪ We wiped away each other's tears ♪

223
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:22,720
♪ But fate was far too cruel ♪

224
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,730
If this marriage must happen,

225
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:42,850
it'll be hard for both Laili and me.

226
00:16:44,180 --> 00:16:46,640
I really don't know what to do.

227
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:56,740
♪ You once said you'd leave one day ♪

228
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:03,530
♪ But I said that day would never come ♪

229
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:12,220
♪ You said if a lover wanders alone ♪

230
00:17:12,710 --> 00:17:17,150
♪ I wouldn't have suffered this much ♪

231
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:25,740
♪ You said if a lover wanders alone ♪

232
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:30,830
♪ I wouldn't have suffered this much ♪

233
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:39,870
♪ Bound together like Laili and Majnun ♪

234
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:46,630
♪ Lingering like lovers,
wasting time away ♪

235
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:53,440
♪ Bound together like Laili and Majnun ♪

236
00:17:54,180 --> 00:18:00,440
♪ Lingering like lovers,
wasting time away ♪

237
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:07,050
♪ We wiped away each other's tears ♪

238
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:12,340
♪ But fate is so cruel ♪

239
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:18,520
It's rare for us to get together.

240
00:18:18,810 --> 00:18:21,290
Too bad Minawar isn't here.

241
00:18:22,090 --> 00:18:23,610
I went away for a while

242
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:24,740
and came back to find out

243
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:26,880
Minawar has become a mother.

244
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,620
Yeah, time flies.

245
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:30,580
She really wanted to come, too.

246
00:18:30,740 --> 00:18:32,010
Does she still dance?

247
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:33,140
She's

248
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:34,770
a bit busy now.

249
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,880
Probably just...

250
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:43,900
My yogurt zongzi is ready.

251
00:18:44,140 --> 00:18:44,940
Sir,

252
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:46,460
have a taste.

253
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:47,840
It's too sweet.

254
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:50,880
Isn't zongzi supposed to be sweet?

255
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:51,480
Let me try.

256
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:54,410
I'm still used to the savory zongzi
from my hometown.

257
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:57,940
It's delicious.

258
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:03,250
When I was in Shanghai,

259
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,660
I was craving the yogurt zongzi
from Kashgar.

260
00:19:05,660 --> 00:19:06,350
Xia Zi.

261
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:08,840
Are you staying in Kashgar

262
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:10,940
for good this time?

263
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:14,310
You were my favorite student back then.

264
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:16,290
Your reading notes

265
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,700
were always the best.

266
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,190
I remember in class,

267
00:19:20,220 --> 00:19:21,980
Arzugul was always the first,

268
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,180
and Fang Nan was always the second.

269
00:19:24,270 --> 00:19:26,730
I gave Fang Nan quite
a lot of extra tutoring.

270
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,850
But he just couldn't score higher
than Xia Zi.

271
00:19:28,850 --> 00:19:30,250
Isn't that frustrating?

272
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:31,530
I even asked him,

273
00:19:31,530 --> 00:19:33,400
"Does Ms. Li tutor you at home?"

274
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,680
He told me no.

275
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:35,460
He's lied.

276
00:19:35,590 --> 00:19:36,500
Do you know?

277
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,740
Back then, he liked a girl in your class.

278
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,660
He secretly made an almond necklace
at home.

279
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:45,200
Even now, I don't know who that girl was.

280
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:45,460
It's ready.

281
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:46,990
Xia Zi, do you know who it is?

282
00:19:47,330 --> 00:19:48,590
I don't know, either.

283
00:19:58,460 --> 00:19:59,860
If at that class reunion,

284
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:02,240
I had been a bit braver,

285
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,270
maybe our child

286
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,560
would be old enough to run errands by now.

287
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,280
I wanted to stay in Shanghai.

288
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:11,570
Maybe we would've broken up
right after graduation.

289
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,770
Or maybe

290
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,250
we didn't.

291
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:18,050
We would have

292
00:20:19,290 --> 00:20:20,460
a very happy family.

293
00:20:22,090 --> 00:20:22,850
Maybe

294
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,860
we would never leave here.

295
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:29,810
Then maybe we'd have gotten sick
of each other by now—

296
00:20:29,810 --> 00:20:30,850
me sick of you,

297
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:31,700
you sick of me.

298
00:20:32,980 --> 00:20:34,380
Or… we could

299
00:20:34,740 --> 00:20:36,470
be happy even while bickering.

300
00:20:41,030 --> 00:20:41,700
Xia Zi.

301
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:48,950
This is for you.

302
00:20:50,020 --> 00:20:51,880
I know you won't accept it easily.

303
00:20:52,010 --> 00:20:53,810
Just consider it my investment.

304
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,280
I heard about Zhou Hengzhi.

305
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,160
Do you really believe

306
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:00,830
he'll come back?

307
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:05,680
I know why you're giving me this money.

308
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:07,600
So I really can't accept it.

309
00:21:08,290 --> 00:21:10,150
When you graduated from college,

310
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:12,410
you had so many good opportunities,

311
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:14,470
yet you still chose to come back here.

312
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:17,510
That day when I saw you treating the lamb,

313
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:19,050
I knew

314
00:21:19,990 --> 00:21:20,950
you belong here.

315
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,650
You can't leave this place.

316
00:21:24,570 --> 00:21:25,970
But you're back now, too.

317
00:21:27,770 --> 00:21:29,810
But I'm not sure where I'll go next.

318
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:34,160
Where my future lies,

319
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:35,290
I don't know.

320
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,900
So I definitely can't take this money.

321
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:39,230
It's good for both of us.

322
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:43,530
I understand.

323
00:21:46,570 --> 00:21:47,770
I won't push you.

324
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:53,900
Xia Zi.

325
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:00,140
This thing—

326
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:03,080
I hope you can accept it.

327
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:09,030
I wanted to give

328
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,730
this almond necklace
to you at the class reunion.

329
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,810
But I kept it for 7 years,

330
00:22:16,370 --> 00:22:17,370
and it got ruined.

331
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:18,850
I fixed it again.

332
00:22:29,350 --> 00:22:30,350
Please accept it.

333
00:22:32,860 --> 00:22:33,920
Once you accept it,

334
00:22:35,970 --> 00:22:37,230
I can finally let it go.

335
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:49,500
Okay,

336
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:51,050
I'll take it.

337
00:22:52,790 --> 00:22:53,700
Now that I've accepted it,

338
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:54,670
you can let it go.

339
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:10,640
Does it look good on me?

340
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:12,770
It does.

341
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,530
Can't she put more effort into this?

342
00:23:31,530 --> 00:23:32,050
Yeah.

343
00:23:32,050 --> 00:23:33,330
The dress size was wrong.

344
00:23:33,330 --> 00:23:34,330
It was too tight.

345
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:37,180
I couldn't even finish my move just now.

346
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,740
Is Gulistan's outfit ready yet?

347
00:23:41,740 --> 00:23:43,380
I need to take it to her.

348
00:23:43,810 --> 00:23:46,140
Too slow.
You're slowing everything down.

349
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:46,940
-I'm sorry.
-Minawar.

350
00:23:46,940 --> 00:23:47,680
Not this one.

351
00:23:47,750 --> 00:23:49,210
One headpiece is missing.

352
00:23:51,110 --> 00:23:52,570
Headpiece, headpiece...

353
00:23:53,010 --> 00:23:55,740
So it's true that you get mom brain
after having a baby.

354
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:57,200
If you slept less than 5 hours a day,

355
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,400
you'd be out of it, too.

356
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:58,980
You...

357
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,760
Stop working. Come with me.

358
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,460
Let's go.

359
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:21,710
What?

360
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:22,570
To eat.

361
00:24:24,980 --> 00:24:26,700
I can't leave now.

362
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,750
Do you want a toy?

363
00:24:54,190 --> 00:24:55,180
Do you want a toy?

364
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,200
I'll get you a toy.

365
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,770
What is this?

366
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:04,460
Diet pills?

367
00:25:04,660 --> 00:25:06,420
Your hair is falling out in handfuls.

368
00:25:06,420 --> 00:25:08,080
You can't take these anymore.

369
00:25:08,850 --> 00:25:10,050
I know you want to keep in shape,

370
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,770
but you shouldn't take this.

371
00:25:12,590 --> 00:25:13,520
Starting today,

372
00:25:14,330 --> 00:25:15,570
we will supervise you.

373
00:25:15,570 --> 00:25:16,400
We'll accompany her

374
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,420
to run and take care of the baby.

375
00:25:17,420 --> 00:25:18,090
Okay.

376
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:19,650
Let's go.

377
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:21,400
Let her sleep a bit.

378
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:27,720
Come on.

379
00:25:31,810 --> 00:25:32,550
Hurry up.

380
00:25:33,550 --> 00:25:34,400
Coming.

381
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,410
It's scorching out here.

382
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,260
You run so fast.

383
00:25:41,530 --> 00:25:42,220
Hurry up.

384
00:25:56,810 --> 00:25:57,530
I can't go on.

385
00:25:57,530 --> 00:25:58,850
You can do it.

386
00:26:12,290 --> 00:26:13,370
Have you thought about it?

387
00:26:13,370 --> 00:26:14,660
If you don't want to get married,

388
00:26:14,660 --> 00:26:15,550
we can help you.

389
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:19,030
Come here.

390
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,240
Look at my new quilt.

391
00:26:21,330 --> 00:26:22,140
Isn't it nice?

392
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:24,180
It's very comfortable.

393
00:26:25,530 --> 00:26:26,400
Feel it.

394
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:28,570
It's comfortable, right?

395
00:26:36,090 --> 00:26:37,140
Come on, come on. Have some pilaf, kids.

396
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:38,660
Eat pilaf.

397
00:26:43,050 --> 00:26:44,770
Who made the pilaf?

398
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:46,250
Her mom made it.

399
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:47,310
It's so delicious.

400
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:48,770
Eat pilaf, kids.

401
00:26:48,770 --> 00:26:50,460
You look so pretty today.

402
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:55,250
Her cooking just keeps getting better.

403
00:26:56,410 --> 00:26:57,150
Laili.

404
00:26:57,700 --> 00:26:58,420
Laili.

405
00:26:59,850 --> 00:27:00,780
Mulading, he...

406
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:06,660
Master, Ma'am,

407
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:08,150
Laili,

408
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:09,580
I'm leaving.

409
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:15,030
Grandma.

410
00:27:15,590 --> 00:27:17,190
Go on, read it, child.

411
00:27:21,420 --> 00:27:22,460
For so many years,

412
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:23,810
thank you for your care.

413
00:27:24,790 --> 00:27:26,090
I'm an orphan,

414
00:27:26,390 --> 00:27:28,450
and you gave me the warmth of a family.

415
00:27:28,630 --> 00:27:29,630
But in the end,

416
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,110
this is not my home.

417
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,870
Rather than a home given to me by others,

418
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:39,730
I want my own home more.

419
00:27:40,550 --> 00:27:43,180
I took the 30,000 yuan betrothal gift.

420
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:46,100
Master, Ma'am, don't blame me.

421
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:49,980
Just take it as compensation
for the slap Master gave me,

422
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:52,810
and Laili's ignoring me.

423
00:27:52,930 --> 00:27:54,720
I won't feel sorry for you,

424
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:56,290
because I truly considered you

425
00:27:56,290 --> 00:27:57,770
my family.

426
00:27:58,310 --> 00:28:00,710
You don't need to feel sorry
for me, either,

427
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:03,230
because I've always been just an outsider.

428
00:28:05,170 --> 00:28:07,300
You've already done more than enough.

429
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:10,240
Dad.

430
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:14,070
Mom.

431
00:28:14,970 --> 00:28:15,770
Grandma.

432
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:26,900
Let's eat first.

433
00:28:27,140 --> 00:28:29,610
Auntie made such a huge spread.

434
00:28:29,830 --> 00:28:30,550
Eat up.

435
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:32,100
Try this naan.

436
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:33,790
-Let's eat.
-Auntie made them this morning.

437
00:28:33,790 --> 00:28:34,640
Let's eat.

438
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:36,170
They're really delicious.

439
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:36,880
Really.

440
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:37,960
Try it.

441
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:38,750
Mom,

442
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:41,570
Dad bought this this morning.

443
00:28:43,900 --> 00:28:44,550
Eat more.

444
00:28:44,810 --> 00:28:45,500
Eat more.

445
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,650
It's delicious.

446
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:11,220
Come on. Let's have a toast.

447
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:12,400
To what?

448
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:14,190
To

449
00:29:14,270 --> 00:29:16,600
the costumes I'll never get to wear again.

450
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,160
Baby.

451
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:19,510
Then...

452
00:29:20,140 --> 00:29:21,000
to the dutar

453
00:29:21,660 --> 00:29:23,530
that I can never play again.

454
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,320
What about you, Arzugul?

455
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,420
Me?

456
00:29:29,140 --> 00:29:31,030
Then I'll toast to

457
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:33,580
the Shanghai

458
00:29:33,610 --> 00:29:35,750
that I might never return to.

459
00:29:36,250 --> 00:29:37,070
Cheers.

460
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:41,250
Who among you

461
00:29:41,330 --> 00:29:43,650
can actually marry a husband
into the family?

462
00:29:43,650 --> 00:29:44,740
Only me.

463
00:29:44,770 --> 00:29:46,370
Only I, Laili, could do that.

464
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,070
Only you.

465
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:49,330
Drink less.

466
00:29:49,330 --> 00:29:51,590
Impressive. I admit you are impressive.

467
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:53,200
You're indeed impressive.

468
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,400
Your groom even ran away at the wedding.

469
00:29:56,310 --> 00:29:58,900
I've only ever heard of runaway brides,

470
00:29:58,900 --> 00:30:01,750
but never a runaway groom.

471
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:04,680
Indeed, not many women
have this kind of experience.

472
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:05,290
Right.

473
00:30:05,290 --> 00:30:07,220
It's so hard.

474
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:09,880
Yeah.

475
00:30:18,610 --> 00:30:20,900
Actually, you are better off than we are.

476
00:30:22,650 --> 00:30:26,090
Because she has 2 good besties
who are more miserable than her,

477
00:30:26,090 --> 00:30:27,030
right?

478
00:30:27,350 --> 00:30:28,590
Am I miserable?

479
00:30:28,630 --> 00:30:30,090
Am I very miserable?

480
00:30:30,850 --> 00:30:31,910
Am I?

481
00:30:31,940 --> 00:30:32,550
You are not.

482
00:30:32,550 --> 00:30:33,180
I am.

483
00:30:33,180 --> 00:30:34,310
You are not, either.

484
00:30:34,850 --> 00:30:36,140
I am. I am, okay?

485
00:30:36,140 --> 00:30:37,000
I am miserable.

486
00:30:37,190 --> 00:30:39,200
I don't want either of you
to have it worse than me.

487
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,090
As for me,

488
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:40,830
I want you

489
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:43,240
to become the absolute

490
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,680
best dancer.

491
00:30:45,380 --> 00:30:46,280
I want you

492
00:30:46,620 --> 00:30:49,660
to become the most skilled
earthenware craftswoman.

493
00:30:52,140 --> 00:30:53,720
None of us should be miserable.

494
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:56,550
Why should we have it bad at all?

495
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,880
Already watered?

496
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:47,650
Hello.

497
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:49,520
My friend.

498
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:56,540
Got your knucklebones on you?

499
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,220
I have them with me.

500
00:32:10,460 --> 00:32:11,590
I said I'd come back,

501
00:32:13,010 --> 00:32:14,270
and I definitely will.

502
00:32:26,420 --> 00:32:29,330
Zhou Hengzhi is back.

503
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:30,500
Zhou Hengzhi,

504
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:31,570
you're finally back.

505
00:32:31,570 --> 00:32:33,960
I thought you lied to Xia Zi

506
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:35,400
and would never return.

507
00:32:36,250 --> 00:32:37,330
Who told you that nonsense?

508
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:38,180
You little brat.

509
00:32:38,180 --> 00:32:39,810
Was it Rejep or Abudu?

510
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:42,070
Neither.

511
00:32:42,070 --> 00:32:43,980
My friend Shirzat told me.

512
00:32:46,140 --> 00:32:48,010
And who is Shirzat?

513
00:32:49,530 --> 00:32:51,000
How do you guys know everything?

514
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,090
You adults are so silly.

515
00:32:53,090 --> 00:32:55,660
You only hear what you want to hear,

516
00:32:55,660 --> 00:32:56,980
but always forget the people and things

517
00:32:56,980 --> 00:32:59,330
closest to you.

518
00:33:00,610 --> 00:33:02,740
You've got an answer for everything.

519
00:33:03,420 --> 00:33:06,680
Little rubber ball, banana, and pear.

520
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:09,750
Maran blossoms—21,

521
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:11,330
25, 26,

522
00:33:11,330 --> 00:33:13,050
25, 27,

523
00:33:13,050 --> 00:33:15,740
28, 29, 31.

524
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,610
Why are we clapping?

525
00:33:18,610 --> 00:33:19,340
I don't know.

526
00:33:21,830 --> 00:33:23,200
What's this?

527
00:33:27,140 --> 00:33:27,940
Where is this?

528
00:33:28,290 --> 00:33:29,020
My hometown.

529
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:30,660
Have you been to Xichang?

530
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:31,420
Never.

531
00:33:31,850 --> 00:33:32,980
It's a plateau, too,

532
00:33:33,070 --> 00:33:34,670
but not as high as the Pamirs.

533
00:33:34,740 --> 00:33:35,810
Are these your parents?

534
00:33:35,810 --> 00:33:36,700
How did you know?

535
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:37,900
They look a bit like you.

536
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:38,900
Those two are really in love—

537
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:40,140
the kind who sing

538
00:33:40,140 --> 00:33:42,000
while doing housework together.

539
00:33:42,140 --> 00:33:42,860
I envy you.

540
00:33:44,050 --> 00:33:45,510
This is my first homestay.

541
00:33:45,510 --> 00:33:47,640
It's in Qingcheng Mountain, Chengdu.

542
00:33:48,310 --> 00:33:49,710
You take such great photos.

543
00:33:49,710 --> 00:33:51,660
Take more when our homestay opens.

544
00:33:53,090 --> 00:33:55,010
This is probably
my swan song in photography.

545
00:33:55,010 --> 00:33:56,580
Where do you think the money came from?

546
00:33:56,580 --> 00:33:57,340
I sold

547
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:59,160
my camera and all my lenses.

548
00:34:00,290 --> 00:34:00,980
Good thing

549
00:34:01,400 --> 00:34:03,860
I bought limited-edition lenses back then.

550
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:05,260
That must've cost you.

551
00:34:07,310 --> 00:34:08,230
I can tell

552
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:11,159
you are already attached to this place.

553
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:25,659
I just snapped it casually.

554
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:27,489
You took quite a few.

555
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,510
I don't think

556
00:34:36,050 --> 00:34:36,980
any of these are as good as this one.

557
00:34:36,980 --> 00:34:37,639
Look,

558
00:34:37,780 --> 00:34:38,780
how natural it is.

559
00:34:39,010 --> 00:34:40,610
I think this one is nice, too.

560
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:41,460
Don't delete it.

561
00:34:41,460 --> 00:34:42,659
I already deleted it.

562
00:34:42,690 --> 00:34:43,510
Do you know

563
00:34:43,510 --> 00:34:46,510
there's a feature called
recently deleted recovery?

564
00:34:46,670 --> 00:34:48,840
If you want to recover it, just do it.

565
00:34:53,010 --> 00:34:54,270
When did you take this?

566
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:59,530
How could I let you know?

567
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:04,020
Here you go.

568
00:35:04,460 --> 00:35:05,190
Send it to me.

569
00:35:06,530 --> 00:35:07,660
I charge for photos.

570
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:12,200
I'll transfer the money.
Let's see if you accept it.

571
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,940
Why are you wearing couple outfits?

572
00:35:31,980 --> 00:35:34,210
What couple outfits?

573
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:35,650
But couple outfits

574
00:35:35,650 --> 00:35:38,450
shouldn't be identical
from head to toe like this.

575
00:35:39,330 --> 00:35:40,660
We think

576
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:44,740
just cutting costs without generating
new income isn't a real solution.

577
00:35:44,780 --> 00:35:46,510
So, we got tour guide licenses.

578
00:35:46,820 --> 00:35:48,950
Pamir Sunny Days

579
00:35:48,970 --> 00:35:50,500
Private Custom Tours.

580
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:51,630
What does this mean?

581
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,050
This is a custom small-group tour

582
00:35:53,050 --> 00:35:54,450
we run in partnership
with a travel agency.

583
00:35:54,350 --> 00:35:55,380
[Kashgar Bus Terminal]

584
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:56,770
Our car is right here.

585
00:35:58,920 --> 00:35:59,730
Here are the hats.

586
00:35:59,730 --> 00:36:00,860
Give me the luggage.

587
00:36:01,500 --> 00:36:02,130
Yours.

588
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:03,550
The kid's.

589
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:07,180
[Yummy Restaurant]

590
00:36:07,260 --> 00:36:08,570
Here's your lamb spine meat.

591
00:36:08,570 --> 00:36:09,340
Ready?

592
00:36:09,340 --> 00:36:09,730
Yes.

593
00:36:11,110 --> 00:36:13,500
Here are your lamb skewers.

594
00:36:13,980 --> 00:36:15,050
Your yogurt.

595
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:16,010
One pilaf?

596
00:36:16,010 --> 00:36:16,500
Okay.

597
00:36:16,820 --> 00:36:17,210
Here.

598
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:21,060
If you think it's good,

599
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:22,800
please give us a five-star review.

600
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:23,610
These earthenwares

601
00:36:23,610 --> 00:36:24,900
are definitely not products made

602
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:26,430
on a factory assembly line.

603
00:36:27,010 --> 00:36:29,130
3, 2, 1.

604
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:32,380
We're here to attend a local wedding?

605
00:36:32,380 --> 00:36:33,520
We have to dance?

606
00:36:34,420 --> 00:36:35,860
Don't be shy, everyone.

607
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:36,840
Dance.

608
00:36:38,770 --> 00:36:40,250
Dance and sing.

609
00:36:45,630 --> 00:36:47,380
You're amazing, sir.

610
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,820
The altitude is over 4,000 meters,

611
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:50,300
and you don't have altitude sickness.

612
00:36:50,300 --> 00:36:51,230
Look, everyone.

613
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:52,780
The road we're driving on now

614
00:36:52,780 --> 00:36:54,110
has more than 600 bends.

615
00:36:54,730 --> 00:36:55,360
They say,

616
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:57,420
if you walk
all the twists and turns today,

617
00:36:57,420 --> 00:36:58,420
your life from now on

618
00:36:58,420 --> 00:36:59,620
will be a smooth path.

619
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:09,590
Sir, ma'am.

620
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,860
Why don't you sit there and rest a bit?

621
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:12,300
It's fine.

622
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:14,030
Don't just keep standing here.

623
00:37:15,590 --> 00:37:16,730
I have water here.

624
00:37:17,010 --> 00:37:17,780
Ma'am,

625
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:18,690
here's some water.

626
00:37:18,690 --> 00:37:19,570
Okay, thanks.

627
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:20,190
Sir,

628
00:37:21,420 --> 00:37:22,010
yours.

629
00:37:22,530 --> 00:37:23,860
It'scorching out here.

630
00:37:24,050 --> 00:37:25,280
Pour some water to cool down.

631
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,000
-Ma'am.
-I can't stand it anymore.

632
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:26,500
Here.

633
00:37:29,610 --> 00:37:30,980
How about we walk towards the road

634
00:37:30,980 --> 00:37:32,150
and go meet Zhou Hengzhi?

635
00:37:32,150 --> 00:37:33,150
I think he'll be here soon.

636
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:33,820
Okay.

637
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:34,940
Come on.

638
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:43,210
Over here.

639
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:48,820
Get in. Get in.

640
00:37:48,820 --> 00:37:49,490
Thanks for waiting.

641
00:37:49,490 --> 00:37:50,290
Sorry.

642
00:37:51,650 --> 00:37:52,460
I'm a bit late.

643
00:37:52,460 --> 00:37:55,920
I just dropped off the guests
from the last tour at the airport.

644
00:38:01,110 --> 00:38:02,750
[Welcome to Kashgar Hotel]

645
00:38:03,380 --> 00:38:04,090
Xia. Xia.

646
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:04,650
Ma'am.

647
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:05,800
I just realized my camera

648
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,880
was left at that photo spot in the desert.

649
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,510
My camera is very expensive.

650
00:38:09,780 --> 00:38:11,310
My photos are in there, too.

651
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:12,860
Ma'am, look.

652
00:38:13,010 --> 00:38:13,820
Calm down.

653
00:38:13,860 --> 00:38:15,120
I'll go look for it now.

654
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:17,090
Please help promote our agency later.

655
00:38:17,090 --> 00:38:18,160
Sure.

656
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:18,880
Thank you.

657
00:38:18,910 --> 00:38:21,370
It's fine.
We'll let you know when we find it.

658
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:24,320
Zhou Hengzhi!

659
00:38:42,910 --> 00:38:43,580
Hello.

660
00:38:44,150 --> 00:38:47,010
The number you dial is not available.

661
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,880
Please dail again later.

662
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:43,400
Are you okay?

663
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:45,960
Why did you come here?
Do you have a death wish?

664
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:48,160
I was afraid you'd be buried by the sand.

665
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,600
The sandstorm is too strong.

666
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:54,900
I don't think we can leave tonight.

667
00:39:57,210 --> 00:39:58,860
You knew there was a sandstorm,

668
00:39:58,860 --> 00:40:00,190
yet you still came here.

669
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:02,400
I was worried sick.

670
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:27,830
Have you heard of the sands
of quantum entanglement?

671
00:40:29,710 --> 00:40:31,820
Two grains of sand split
from the same rock—

672
00:40:31,820 --> 00:40:33,530
even if they are worlds apart，

673
00:40:35,130 --> 00:40:36,420
when one is touched,

674
00:40:36,650 --> 00:40:39,580
the other will resonate
at the exact same frequency.

675
00:40:41,980 --> 00:40:44,510
People parting ways
each hold a grain of sand.

676
00:40:44,570 --> 00:40:46,210
When one misses the other,

677
00:40:46,550 --> 00:40:49,010
the other's grain
will tremble in response.

678
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:55,220
You just made that up, didn't you?

679
00:40:56,710 --> 00:40:57,950
Not entirely.

680
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,980
Part of it actually
has a scientific basis.

681
00:41:10,210 --> 00:41:12,070
When we wake up tomorrow morning,

682
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:15,090
we'll not be buried in the sand, right?

683
00:41:26,650 --> 00:41:27,590
I'm sorry.

684
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,330
I dragged you into this.

685
00:41:37,590 --> 00:41:38,400
What's wrong?

686
00:41:38,990 --> 00:41:40,920
Why are you looking at me like that?

687
00:41:41,090 --> 00:41:42,370
Is... Is there something

688
00:41:42,370 --> 00:41:43,160
on my face?

689
00:41:45,730 --> 00:41:47,930
You're still joking at a time like this?

690
00:41:48,010 --> 00:41:49,470
You're really something.

691
00:41:56,210 --> 00:41:57,810
I was really scared just now.

692
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,720
I was afraid you'd be like my dad,

693
00:42:00,830 --> 00:42:01,890
never coming back.

694
00:42:16,070 --> 00:42:17,090
Xia Zi

695
00:42:22,060 --> 00:42:22,850
I...

696
00:42:27,610 --> 00:42:29,640
I don't want us to just be friends.
